==Society and culture==
Many [[pseudoscience|pseudoscientific]] claims by proponents of [[alternative medicine]] surround the topic of candidiasis. Oral candidiasis is sometimes presented in this manner to be a symptom of a widely prevalent "systemic candidiasis", "candida hypersensitivity syndrome", "yeast allergy", or "gastrointestinal candida overgrowth", which are medically unrecognized conditions. (See: [[Candidiasis#Society and culture]].)

